data.title: Anna Lenhardt, William Lee III
data.meta_description: The bride helps opera singers learn business skills, and the bridegroom advises companies about estate strategies.
data.text:
Anna Rachael Lenhardt and William Russell Lee III were married Saturday in New York. Msgr. Robert Romano performed the ceremony at the Church of St. Thomas More.

Mrs. Lee, 30, is the founder and executive director of Opera Singers Initiative, a nonprofit organization in New York that teaches business skills to opera singers. She is the manager of administration and human resources at TCC Group, a management consultancy in New York that provides planning and advice to foundations. She graduated from New Mexico State University and received a masterâ€™s in vocal performance from New York University.

She is a daughter of Cheryl Lenhardt and Randy Lenhardt of Deming, N.M.

Mr. Lee, 32, is an associate director at Cushman & Wakefield, the commercial real estate company, where he represents and advises companies on estate strategy. He works in New York. He graduated from Fordham.

He is a son of Nancy Spielberg of San Francisco and Mr. Lee II of Pleasantville, Calif. The bridegroom is a stepson of Jack Spielberg.
